This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dialog systems. It may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of neural networks and transfer learning. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it discusses the development of a framework for building cross-lingual dialog systems. Finally, it may also be relevant to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it addresses the need for providing cross-lingual customer support in a globalized world.
